<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" lang="en" xml:lang="en">
  <head>
    <title>ToDo App</title>
    <link href="/style.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <script src="/index.js"></script>
  </head>
  <body>
<main>
<section>
  <h1 class="title">BrokeSmoke</h1>
  <h3 class="ondertitel">Keep track of your smoking habits</h3>
</section>
<p class="screenreader">
  This website is for people who would like to smoke less and want to begin with having more insight in how much they actually smoke.
  As quitting cold turkey isn't the most suitable solution for everyone, this website will not contain quitting as a main goal, but choosing not to light one up.
  To keep the balance at a positive number, you'll have to smoke half as much as usual.

  First, there'll be a short overview of the current status.
</p>


<section class="money">
  <section class="left">
    <p> Smoked less:  <%= saves %> </p>
    <p> Have smoked:  <%= smokes %> </p>
    <p> Scrounged off:  <%= scrounges %> </p>
  </section>
  <section class="right">
    <p class="balance">Balance: € <%= ((saves * 0.35)+(smokes * -0.35)+(scrounges * -0.35)).toFixed(2) %>  </p>
    <p> Total spent: € <%= ((smokes * 0.35)+(scrounges * 0.35)).toFixed(2) %> </p>
    <p> Total saved: €  <%= (saves * 0.35).toFixed(2) %> </p>
  </section>
</section>

<p class="screenreader">
  Now, first thing that's up is the three categories; savings, smokes and scroungers. Not smoking and saving one, smoking one and giving a cigarette away.
  You can increase and decrease your current amount with the two buttons.
</p>

<div class="categories">
  <section class="savings">
    <h2>  <%= saves %> Cigarettes saved</h2>
    <h3>€ <%= (saves * 0.35).toFixed(2) %> </h3>
    <div class="savedimg ">
      <% include smallSaved.svg %>
    </div>
    <section class="buttons">
    <form action="/removesave" method="POST">
      <button class="remove">remove savings</button>
    </form>
    <form action="/addsave" method="POST">
      <button>add savings</button>
    </form>
  </section>
  </section>



  <section class="smokes">
    <h2>  <%= smokes %> Cigarettes smoked</h2>
    <h3>€ <%= (smokes * 0.35).toFixed(2) %> </h3>
    <div class="savedimg ">
      <% include smallSmoked.svg %>
    </div>
    <section class="buttons">
      <form action="/removesmoke" method="POST">
        <button class="remove">remove smokes</button>
      </form>
      <form action="/addsmoke" method="POST">
        <button>add smokes</button>
      </form>
    </section>
  </section>



  <section class="scrounges">
    <h2>  <%= scrounges %> Cigarettes scrounged </h2>
    <h3>€ <%= (scrounges * 0.35).toFixed(2) %> </h3>
    <div class="savedimg ">
      <% include smallScrounged.svg %>
    </div>
    <section class="buttons">
    <form action="/removescrounge" method="POST">
      <button class="remove">remove scrounge</button>
    </form>
        <form action="/addscrounge" method="POST">
          <button>add scrounge</button>
        </form>
  </section>
  </section>
</div>

<p class="screenreader">
  Last, there's a section that contains the visual representation on your smoking habits. It's basically one big pile of cigarettes that's increasing.
</p>

<h3>The Big Ol' Stack of Cigarettes</h3>
<p> You know, in case you wanna scroll through your total smoking progress.</p>
<section class="cigarettesVisualized">

          <%  for (i = 0; i < saves; i++) { %>
            <% include smallSaved.svg %>
          <%  } %>

  <%  for (i = 0; i < smokes; i++) { %>
    <% include smallSmoked.svg %>
  <%  } %>

  <%  for (i = 0; i < scrounges; i++) { %>
    <% include smallScrounged.svg %>
  <%  } %>
</section>


    </main>
  </body>
</html>
